PL/SQL (Procedural Language/SQL) is Oracle's extension of SQL that combines SQL commands with programming features such as variables, loops, 
conditions, procedures, and exception handling.

Simple Definition
SQL → Used to query and manipulate data.
PL/SQL → Used to write complete programs that interact with the database.

Example

SQL

SELECT salary
FROM employees
WHERE emp_id = 101;

PL/SQL

DECLARE
    v_salary NUMBER;
BEGIN
    SELECT salary
    INTO v_salary
    FROM employees
    WHERE emp_id = 101;

    DBMS_OUTPUT.PUT_LINE('Salary: ' || v_salary);
END;
